This project demonstrates how to deploy an Amazon EC2 instance using Terraform while enforcing strict security and validation checks. By using `precondition` blocks, we ensure that the infrastructure is only built if it meets our specified criteria (such as valid AMI architectures and allowed instance types) before AWS resources are ever provisioned.

